description:
## Severity
Critical
## Dimension
error-handling
## Location
src/tui/app.rs:480-497
## Violation
The transcript persistence loop breaks on the first append error but unconditionally sets the watermark to `session_messages.len()` afterward. Every message in the tail past the failure point is silently skipped on the next call — permanent transcript data loss.

```rust
fn persist_transcript_tail(&mut self) {
    let cwd = self.transcript_cwd.clone();
    let session_id = self.chat_session.id.clone();
    for msg in &self.session_messages[self.transcript_watermark..] {
        ...
        if let Err(err) = crate::transcript::append_entry(&cwd, &session_id, &entry) {
            tracing::warn!(error = %err, "transcript append failed");
            break;
        }
    }
    self.transcript_watermark = self.session_messages.len();  // BUG: advances past failed messages
}
```

If `append_entry` fails on the 3rd message of 10, the loop breaks but the watermark jumps to 10. The 4th-10th messages will never be retried — they are dropped from the transcript permanently. The warn log gives no hint that 7 entries were lost.

## Mandated refactor
Track successful appends in a counter and advance the watermark by that amount only:

```rust
let mut appended = 0usize;
for msg in &self.session_messages[self.transcript_watermark..] {
    ...
    match crate::transcript::append_entry(&cwd, &session_id, &entry) {
        Ok(()) => appended += 1,
        Err(err) => {
            tracing::warn!(error = %err, appended, remaining = self.session_messages.len() - self.transcript_watermark - appended, "transcript append failed");
            break;
        }
    }
}
self.transcript_watermark += appended;
```

